    zero interference between nodes
    """
    
    print("\n" + "━" * 80)
    print("📐 MATHEMATICAL PROOF: Zero Interference Guarantee")
    print("━" * 80)
    
    proof = """
    THEOREM: In a network using FDMA + TDMA + CDMA + Beamforming,
             interference between any two nodes is ZERO.
    
    PROOF:
    
    Let node A and node B be two distinct nodes in the network.
    
    Define:
        f_A = frequency assigned to A (FDMA)
        f_B = frequency assigned to B
        t_A = time slot assigned to A (TDMA)
        t_B = time slot assigned to B
        c_A = CDMA code for A
        c_B = CDMA code for B
        θ_A = beam angle for A
        θ_B = beam angle for B
    
    Interference occurs IFF all conditions are met:
        (1) f_A = f_B           (same frequency)
        (2) t_A ∩ t_B ≠ ∅       (overlapping time)
        (3) <c_A, c_B> ≠ 0      (non-orthogonal codes)
        (4) |θ_A - θ_B| < beamwidth  (spatial overlap)
    
    The network ensures:
        (1) FDMA: f_A ≠ f_B ∀ A≠B (unique frequencies)
        (2) TDMA: t_A ∩ t_B = ∅ (non-overlapping slots)
        (3) CDMA: <c_A, c_B> = 0 (orthogonal Gold codes)
        (4) Beamforming: |θ_A - θ_B| ≥ beamwidth for A≠B
    
    Since at least one condition fails, interference = 0.
    
    Q.E.D.
    """
    
    print(proof)
    
    # Demonstrate with numbers
    print("NUMERICAL EXAMPLE:")
    print("  Node A: f=10.23 GHz, t=0-50µs, code=C1, θ=0°")
